did.unittitle: Stanford University, Office of Student Activities and Leadership, records
did.abstract: Correspondence, memos, minutes, reports, lists, guidelines, policies, printed materials, registrations, constitutions, and other records pertaining to the administration of student organizations on campus and support services provided by the Office of Student Activities and Leadership (and its predecessors, the Office of Student Activities, and Student Organization Services ) including space allocation, funding, custodial services, maintenance, and leadership retreats. Collection also includes information files on fraternities and sororities, 1943-2003.

repository.label: Repository:
repository.corpname: Department of Special Collections and University Archives

acqinfo.p: Materials were transferred from the Office of Student Activities and Leadership, and its predecessor the Office of Student Activities, from 1989 through 2014.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Ownership & Copyright
userestrict.p: All requests to reproduce, publish, quote from, or otherwise use collection materials must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, California 94304-6064. Consent is given on behalf of Special Collections as the owner of the physical items and is not intended to include or imply permission from the copyright owner. Such permission must be obtained from the copyright owner, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/depts/spc/pubserv/permissions.html.
Restrictions also apply to digital representations of the original materials. Use of digital files is restricted to research and educational purposes.

prefercite.head: Cite As

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical Sketch
bioghist.p: The Office of Student Activities and Leadership, under the jurisdiction of the Office of Student Affairs, provides information and assistance to students on organizing their groups and activities. Previously known as the Office of Student Activities, under the jurisdiction of the Campus Affairs Office. Previous to November 1990, it was known as Student Organization Services.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Collection
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, memos, minutes, reports, lists, guidelines, policies, printed materials, registrations, constitutions, and other records pertaining to the administration of student organizations on campus and support services provided by the Office of Student Activities and Leadership (and its predecessors, the Office of Student Activities, and Student Organization Services ) including space allocation, funding, custodial services, maintenance, and leadership retreats. Collection also includes information files on fraternities and sororities, 1943-2003.

bioghist.p: Student Organization Services (SOS) was a division of the Campus Affairs Office, which was one of the administrative offices of the Dean of Student Affairs. SOS was responsible for authorizing all student organizations at Stanford, articulating and implementing relevant University policies, and providing services to student organizations.

scopecontent.p: These records pertain to the administration of student organizations and services provided to them by the Student Organization Services including space allocation, funding, custodial services, maintenance, and leadership retreats. Included are correspondence, memos, minutes, reports, lists, guidelines, policies, and printed materials.
